sentences: Billy Watkins (1927-2010) was a gospel and soul singer who later became a Christian minister.
Watkins was born to parents Bartha Lillard Watkins and Priscilla Kinard on July 25, 1927.
When he was 11 years old, he and his family The family moved to California.
Known as Bartha L. Watkins, he was a member The Zion Travelers, a group that was formed in 1944 and first recorded in late 1947.

By October 1959, Wakins had a record out on the Challenge label.
The record "You're Unforgettable" bw "Rendezvous" which Billboard predicted could do well was charting locally that year.
By October 1966, he had "Little Things Mean a Lot" out on the Chattahoochee label which was a Hot 100 prediction.
Having toured throughout the United States, Europe, the Orient and Australia, and having some chart success, it was in the early 1970s that he decided to make a change both musically and spiritually.
He would later become an ordained pastor and establish the Freedom of Spirit Church, a non-denominational church in South Central Los Angeles.
Watkins died at Centinela Hospital Medical Center Medical at Inglewood California on January 24, 2010.
